The restaurant is located in the Sheepshead Bay section of Brooklyn.  They prepare primarily Japanese cuisine.  I ordered the shrimp wonton soup.  The wontons were small and each contained one baby shrimp.  The bento box with salmon teriyaki and sesame chicken was not good.  The salmon was average.  I could not eat the chicken.  It was overcooked and extremely chewy.  The California roll fell apart as I attempted to eat it with my chopstix.  The poke bowl special had some fish and several items on top.  Approximately 90% of the bowl was filled with average tasting white rice.  The Malaysian noodles was average and spicy.  The menu did not indicate that this is a spicy dish.
Very disappointing and above average in price for this food.

I have been coming here for more than 10 years and it has been my favorite sushi place by far. The volcano salad is amazing, the crispy calamari is really good too. Any rolls you get will be delicious. The ambiance is very nice and the staff is kind as well. It is also affordable. I will continue coming here for the next 10 years.

We have ordered food from this place several times already. This time we ordered Chef's Special Roll. The rolls were terrible! Shapeless. Flabby. It was obvious that the cook was in a hurry. We also ordered Tom Yum soup. What they poured into a jar cannot be called soup. And it certainly cannot be called Tom Yum. It is a broth with mushrooms, tomatoes, greens and two shrimps floating in it. Maybe it all happened this way because we ordered on Friday evening. But for me as a regular customer, it does not matter when I place an order. I want to receive a quality product regardless of the cook's workload. I will repeat that we have ordered food before and it was better. Most likely, I will not order food from this place anymore. To clarify: I placed the order online. I picked up the order myself. The order fulfillment time is accurate.

This hidden gem of a sushi restaurant offers top-notch, fresh dishes and exceptional service. Highly recommended for a delightful dining experience.
